   {:e #blake3 "dc330838f702659e609d1dacc77a5e7c8149ef00f409fd07e63649e386dc8586" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "ADDITIONAL REVIEW ITEM — Tension 7: The Verification Bootstrap Paradox. WITNESS system exists but has zero data because trace scanning isn't in the workflow. Harvest should auto-trigger trace scan. This closes the bilateral loop: harvest → trace scan → witness population → F(S) reflects real verification state → guidance improves. Without this, WITNESS is dead infrastructure. The fix: add trace_scan_and_witness() as a harvest side-effect (SEED.md §5: harvest is semi-automated). This is the same pattern as ZCM-1 (auto-observe) applied to verification: zero-cost witnessing.; Session entity: :task/t-81aa964b; Session entity: :task/t-0b422751; Session entity: :task/t-a739fcbf; Session entity: :task/t-faeed44a; Session entity: :task/t-79a347b9; Session entity: :task/t-afd6ba0b; Session entity: :task/t-9e575667; Session entity: :task/t-efcdcfab; SESSION-028 DOG-FOODING DEEP ANALYSIS: Six structural tensions identified — (1) Heisenberg principle: observation costs execution tokens, solution: store comonad auto-fingerprinting. (2) Triple reconstruction: 3 store loads per CLI call, solution: incremental indexes + OnceCell + daemon. (3) Harvest urgency split-brain: signal_1 uses :harvest/agent, signal_2 uses :harvest/boundary-tx — different baselines, solution: canonical :system/harvest-clock entity. (4) Basin competition: methodology footer costs 50 tokens competing with execution, solution: single-token basin activation. (5) Task-impl traceability gap: tasks stay open after implementation, solution: TaskWitness behavioral binding. (6) Mode-insensitive gap counting: gaps increase during productive work, solution: divergence urgency tensor U(type, phase). UNIFYING PRINCIPLE: All six are residual process obligations not yet structuralized. The project's own axiom (coherence as structure not process) is its fix specification.; Session entity: :task/t-e3810ab1; Session entity: :task/t-0d684fc2; Session entity: :task/t-0305b123; CRYSTALLIZATION PHASE START: Converting 7-tension deep analysis into formal spec elements and comprehensive task graph. Each tension maps to reconciliation taxonomy divergence type. Priority: (1) harvest urgency split-brain bug, (2) harvest-triggered trace scan, (3) store performance, (4) session-scoped M(t), (5) phase-gated gaps, (6) methodology token, (7) task witnesses.; Session entity: :task/t-35e7e275; Session entity: :task/t-e0e03043; Session entity: :task/t-496830d0; CRYSTALLIZATION COMPLETE: 7 EPICs created with 20 granular subtasks for the dog-fooding tension analysis. Each EPIC maps to one tension from the first-principles analysis: (T3) Harvest Urgency Canonical Boundary — P0 bug fix, 3 subtasks. (T7) Verification Bootstrap — P0 highest leverage, 4 subtasks closing the bilateral loop. (T2) Store Performance — P1 daily friction, 4 subtasks eliminating quadruple reconstruction. (T1) Session-Scoped M(t) — P1 broken metric, 2 subtasks. (T6) Phase-Gated Gap Reporting — P1 noise reduction, 2 subtasks. (T4) Rate-Distortion Methodology Token — P2 basin competition, 1 subtask. (T5) Task-Implementation Witnesses — P2 re-discovery prevention, 2 subtasks. Plus: 1 master E2E test, 1 META dependency task. Critical path: T3 → T7 → T1 → T4. Parallel: T2, T6, T5 (after T7). UNIFYING PRINCIPLE: every fix migrates a process obligation to a structural property, completing the axiological commitment of SEED.md §1.; Session entity: :task/t-62bf0ff6; Session entity: :task/t-ef63a4b4; Session entity: :task/t-e8351808; Session entity: :task/t-66197c83; Session entity: :task/t-4301c75e; Session entity: :task/t-60d86eff\nSession entity: :task/t-cf23a686; Session entity: :task/t-05487365; Session entity: :task/t-c193e691; Session entity: :task/t-dad64d2a; Session entity: :task/t-299f5fab; Session entity: :task/t-0608d559; Session entity: :task/t-0c0b8239" :op :assert}
